Never in my wildest dreams did I think I’d land at ScoopWhoop like this. No CV, no long emails, no networking tactics—just me doing what I do best: RANTING. One minute, I was passionately complaining about life, pop culture, and overpriced coffee; the next minute, BOOM—I’m in a place where ranting is practically a job requirement. Life has a funny way of working out, doesn’t it?
